value.value: Adult brain-intrinsic neuron with its soma in the brain, posterior-lateral to the lateral horn (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It has postsynapses in the ipsilateral superior lateral protocerebrum, the ipsilateral posterior lateral protocerebrum, the contralateral superior lateral protocerebrum and the ipsilateral superior clamp (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). There are approximately 6 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

definition.value: Uncharacterized putative cell type based on Hemibrain data (Scheffer et al., 2020) and updated using FlyWire (FAFB) data (Dorkenwald et al., 2024). Soma locations are based on the closest annotated neuropil region. Pre- or post-synapse locations are the fewest regions that collectively contain at least 80 percent of all pre- or post-synapses of these neurons in FlyWire. Neurotransmitter predictions are from Eckstein et al. (2024). Other annotations are based on annotations in FlyWire and are available in the supplemental material of Schlegel et al. (2024).
